data.description: Beautifully updated home in the Oakfield Subdivision. Its location is the first plus to many in this wonderful family home. It is just minutes from downtown and most of Rome's shopping and schools. The home has 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, and the laundry room upstairs. The master bedroom is oversized and the master bathroom was updated within the last year. The bath updates included new his and her vanities, beautiful tile floor, and a large tiled shower. The main level is an entertainers dream. It includes an office space, separate 8-10 person dining room, a living room with a gas fireplace, a breakfast or sitting area, and an updated kitchen with island and stainless steel appliances. There is also a half bath on this level for guests. Just outside the breakfast area back door you will find a deck that overlooks the fenced in back yard and pool. The property goes well past the fence to a creek in the back. You could clear the undergrowth out to extend your back yard, or to get views of the creek that adjoins the rear of the property. In the basement there is an additional finished space. It is open and could be used as an additional bedroom or living room. There is also unfinished space that is currently being used for storage and a full bath. So many possibilities in the basement! The entry door in the basement takes you to a concrete patio and the pool. Come see this one quick, it wont last long!!
